The former governor of Osun state and Minister of Interior, Rauf Aregbesola, shortly after the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC), declared Sanator Ademola Adeleke of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) as winner of the Saturday governorship election, posted a Bible verse that generated reaction on his
He wrote: Osun Le Tente
“This matter is by the decree of the watchers, and the demand by the word of the holy ones: to the intent that the living may know that the most High ruleth in the kingdom of men, and giveth it to whomever he will, and setteth up over it the basest of men.” (Daniel 4:17).
Responses that followed his post include: Jimoh Tajudeen Olawale wrote: “It is now for you to declare and decamp openly sir. So that people would now know where you really belong sir.”
Temidayo Michael Adeleye wrote: “Congratulations Sir, it’s time to resign and leave their Yeye minister position for them..,because it is overused now that you are no longer a member of APC.
READ ALSO: Jubilation in Ede as Ademola Adeleke emerges Osun governor
Oyetunji said, “He taught them a brutal lesson in politics: nobody is indispensable.
Ojoye Samson Oluwagbemiga wrote: “A house divided against itself can never stand.you have played your role in pulling down your own house,  that is all you can achieve. Congratulations you won.”
Funmilayo Aiyeola wrote: “You are right. In The Osun state election I hope and pray Adeleke believes in education like you do. Ogbeni Rauf Aregbesola I love you very much, you are a kind, honest and peaceful person.
Oluwanifemi Eyibobola: “You’ve done your part, I was firm believer in your idea thinking you could put aside bitterness and work for the party, anyway lesson well learnt.”
